{"id":14881267,"mediaExerciseId":"7535034c-3c01-4702-bf60-26ee35247502","exerciseName":"33","chapterName":"10","chapterTitle":"Making Capital Investment Decisions","groupId":612342,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":346,"solutions":[{"id":6327828,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will solve for how many miles it will take before upgrading to another car becomes the logical choice for the firm. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"In order to solve this problem, we will first solve for the annual consumption of gas for each car. To do this, we will simply divide the annual miles driven by the miles per gallon. \n\nFor the car:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Annual consumption of gas}&=\\dfrac{12,000}{25}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=480\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThis means that the current car consumes $480$ gallons per year","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"For the truck:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Annual consumption of gas}&=\\dfrac{12,000}{10}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=1,200\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThis means the current truck consumes $1,200$ gallons per year","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"It would then be ideal to upgrade car if it consumes the same amount of gas as the truck. To solve for the mileage at which this occurs, we can simply multiply the annual consumption of the gas by the miles per gallon of the upgraded car.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Break-even miles}&=1,200 \\times 40\\ \\text{miles per gallon}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=48,000\\ \\text{miles}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nFor the car upgrade to be justified, you need to drive at least $48,000$ miles. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"75b19714-a7fd-44ad-8172-4aa9a1460449","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881268,"exerciseName":"34","page":346,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"716c4d84-420d-441f-afc4-f001472648fe","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-questions-and-problems-34-716c4d84-420d-441f-afc4-f001472648fe"},{"id":14881270,"exerciseName":"36","page":347,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7b055f2f-7312-4ce3-adc3-4ef0c29a7b71","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-questions-and-problems-36-7b055f2f-7312-4ce3-adc3-4ef0c29a7b71"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881266,"exerciseName":"32","page":346,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2965f92a-8f9e-448b-8a0c-8282e2b134f5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-10-questions-and-problems-32-2965f92a-8f9e-448b-8a0c-8282e2b134f5"},{"id":14881265,"exerciseName":"31","page":345,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExer